30/09/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- UN tribunal President Theodor Meron urged Croatia on Wednesday (29 September) to intensify its efforts to locate fugitive indictee General Ante Gotovina.
During a meeting with Croatian Justice Minister Vesna Skare-Ozbolt, the two discussed unresolved issues of co-operation and the possibility of transferring some cases to Croatian courts.
Skare-Ozbolt said the government is committed to finding and arresting Gotovina.
(HINA, HRT - 29/09/04)
